==Italian==

===Etymology===
''Sordino'' and varients come from the words ''[[sorda]]'', ''[[sordo]]'', and ''[[sordamente]]'', all of which mean "dull in tone, muffled".

===Noun===
{{it-noun|sordini|m|o|i}}

# A [[mute]]; a [[sordine]]. For example, the mute instrument for the violin or the [[damper]] on the [[pianforte]].

